I dont believe Powell was wrong. Only a small portion of mkt drop likely rate related. The Fed Funds market attaches less than 1/4 chance of any rate rise next year. It also predicts 6% chance of rate drop in March and a 12% chance of rate rise in March. Rates not problem.

Look at ten year yield! Relying on monetary ease (zero real int rates) is the acme of fragility and vulnerability. Raising rates, even though should have been done three plus years ago, produces short term pain but long term gain.

The portfolio managers clamor for easy money, it makes their job easy. They are lazy. Had ten years of it - and now they claim fault with fed? Rising rates cleanse. They should look in the mirror, Sully @SullyCNBC And face the enemy, it is them.

@realmoney Dec 26, 2018 | 10:03 AM EST DOUG KASS Rate Hike Odds I continue to believe, unlike many, that Powell and the Federal Reserve are only having a limited impact on the market's recent swoon. In defense of my view is that the rate hike odds have fallen to under 25%

for just one rate increase in 2019. Moreover, the odds of a rate reduction in March (according to the Fed Funds futures market) is up to 7% and the odds of a rate increase in March is down to only 12%-13%. @ritholtz @cnbcfastmoney @SullyCNBC
